title: ICE in rustdoc: 'called `Option::unwrap()` on a `None` value', src/librustdoc/clean/auto_trait.rs:356:26

labels.name: T-rustdoc
labels.description: Relevant to the rustdoc team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: regression-from-stable-to-beta
labels.description: Performance or correctness regression from stable to beta.

body:
### Code ```rust // struct Peekable use std::iter::Peekable; pub struct Span { inner: Peekable>, } struct ConditionalIterator { f: F, } impl Iterator for ConditionalIterator { type Item = (); fn next(&mut self) -> Option { todo!() } } ``` ### Meta No crash in stable 1.62.1, crashes with nightly 85b500cca 2022-07-24 and 1b57946a4 2022-08-03 `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.64.0-nightly (1b57946a4 2022-08-03) binary: rustc commit-hash: 1b57946a405d5b2a87e612335db033edb2c3427f commit-date: 2022-08-03 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.64.0-nightly LLVM version: 14.0.6 ``` ### Error output ``` thread 'rustc' panicked at 'called `Option::unwrap()` on a `None` value', src/librustdoc/clean/auto_trait.rs:356:26 ```
